Metatron's Cube No.9. 12" x 12" pyrography on birch top with resin finish. Status: Available. Well, here's my first pyro-cube...and I LOVE it!!! I was hesitant about trying Metatron's Cube in Pyrography, simply for the fact that there are alot of very tight lines, and I was worried it could look sloppy if I wasn't clean with my linework. I'm very happy with how it turned out, and I'm glad I tried it. I left the details to a respectable minimum, to allow the woodgrain to be evident through the pattern. I can definitely see more of these in the future, however I'm already working on my next piece, so stay tuned for that one! If you're interested in this one please send me a direct message and let's chat!

Ya know, sometimes I’m a total space case. 👽 Totally just forgot to take this #wip off the punty before cycling the kiln last night. 🤦‍♀️ Back into the kiln it goes- I guess I won’t be finishing up the sandblasting on it until tomorrow. 
On another note- sorry for this gross picture of my hand, but this is something new I’ve been dealing with for several weeks.. the dermatologist I spoke to in texts says it looks like dyshydrotic eczema exacerbated by excessive hand sweating but my actual appointment with him isn’t until September. Basically what I first thought was an initially unnoticed burn blister on my hand (a pretty common occurrence for me) did not heal like a burn but has instead turned into more and more tiny blisters that keep breaking, peeling and reforming over the palm of my left hand (just the left! 🤷‍♀️) It is clearly pretty uncomfortable and seems to get worse every time I work on the torch for a long period 😓. Obviously I’m not going to stop working and sweaty hands comes with the territory. I have been putting rose salve on it which has only seemed to help with the blisters cracking open less often. 
Sorry to be going on about my gross crusty mitt, but everyone I know with eczema has pretty much had it their whole life and it seems weird to me that this has just popped up out of nowhere on just one spot of my hand, seemingly glassblowing related so I wanted to ask- Any other glassblower out there ever developed or dealt with something like this before?? Anyone got any advice for me other than go see a dermatologist? 
Thanks for reading. 🖐
.
.
